<BaseLayout title="About — Brookings View"
  description="Why Brookings View exists and how it's put together.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About Brookings View</h1>

    <p>Brookings Register, the town's newspaper, closed in August 2025. Since
    then, there's been no single place to find out what the city council
    decided, what's happening at the library this week, or when the Jackrabbits
    play next. Brookings View is an attempt to fill that gap.</p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>The site is built and updated automatically. Every hour, it checks the
    city's and county's public meeting agendas, the library's event calendar,
    SDSU's athletics schedule, the National Weather Service, and USDA market
    data. New information is summarized in plain language and published — no
    person reviews each item before it goes live.</p>
    <p>Read the full breakdown, source by source, on
    <a href="/how-we-gather-this">how we gather this</a>.</p>

    <h2>What you won't find here</h2>
    <p>Brookings View doesn't cover arrests, court records, or obituaries.
    That's a deliberate choice, not an oversight: this site exists to tell you
    what's happening in your town, not to follow anyone through a hard moment
    in their life. If you're looking for that kind of coverage, you won't find
    it — by design.</p>

    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>Automated summaries occasionally get something wrong. If you spot an
    error, <a href="/contact">let us know</a> and we'll fix it.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

